# Example: Proxmox VM with GPU passthrough (GTX 1070) for a Kubernetes worker.
# Copy into infrastructure-provisioning/terraform/environments/homelab/ or a new workspace,
# merge with your proxmox_vm module, and set PCI passthrough in Proxmox UI (host config).
#
# Prerequisites:
# - IOMMU enabled on host, GPU bound to vfio or passed to VM
# - Proxmox: add PCI device (GPU) to VM as passthrough
# - Inside guest: NVIDIA driver + nvidia-container-toolkit; on K8s: NVIDIA GPU Operator
#
# This file is NOT a complete root module — it shows variables you might add alongside existing VM defs.

# Example variables (conceptual):
# gpu_worker_vm_id   = 210
# gpu_worker_cores   = 8
# gpu_worker_memory  = 16384
# gpu_worker_disk_gi = 100   # prefer NVME_STORAGE_FAST1 for OS + container layers

# After VM exists, join it to the cluster (kubeadm join or Rancher custom command),
# label: kubectl label node <name> nvidia.com/gpu.present=true
# Install GPU Operator: helm install ... nv/gpu-operator
